ERSON: THE RELUCTANT LIBRARIAN.     ANDERSON'S 'RELUCTANCE' STEMS FROM HIS TRANSFER FROM THE NEW SOUTH WALESDEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE TO THE HEADSHIP OF THE FREE PUBLIC LIBRARY, SYDNEY,DURING THE AGRICULTURAL RECESSION IN 1893. DESPITE HIS LACK OF PREVIOUSEXPERIENCE IN THE FIELD, ANDERSON MADE HIS MARK AS AN ADMINISTRATOR, IN THETECHNIQUES OF LIBRARIANSHIP, AND IN COLLECTION DEVELOPMENT. THE LIBRARYASSOCIATION OF AUSTRALIA'S H.C.L. ANDERSON AWARD IS CONFERRED FOR 'OUTSTANDINGSERVICE TO LIBRARIANSHIP OR TO THE LIBRARY PROFESSION IN AUSTRALIA'